2022 was a year that I will look back on and smile. I matured as a person but also as a leader more in 12 months than in my previous 27 years combined. There are so many incredible moments, memories, trips, friendships made, families helped.  
 
 
From podcasting with Brad Lea and making a 2,000 bet that I don’t have Exma - To getting verified ( than unverified, First person ever ? ) 
 
To expanding down to Florida.  
Mending relationships. Taking care of those who helped me along the way. To seeing the individuals on the team grow up, mature, win awards and be recognized for their hard work and dedication. To winning bethpages best team on Long Island. To starting the Dan oneil foundation and giving back more than $50,000 to people in need. To becoming the 2023 YPN president, selling my dream house, buying my dream car ( after 3 years don’t chirp me ) to meeting Emily- spending the summer in Montauk. I was on a total of ten plane rides before 2022. 94 flights later ( and probably 200 cancelled ).  
 
Looking at my crumpled up goals for this year, being able to accomplish some, and falling short of many. I can say 2022 will also go down as the year I made the most mistakes. But those mistakes are all lessons I have learned from and will carry with me the rest of my life. 2022 will always have a special place in my heart.  
 
If you’ve read this far you should be thrown in jail . But  know I appreciate you very much and I promise you, anything is possible if you surround yourself with the right people and work hard enough. 2023 let’s go!!

Happy Sunday family. I always say I wish I had a go pro on my head at all times because most of what happens you would have to see to believe. ( IE. the door assaulting me last week, getting stuck in the elevator etc ). But this one takes the cake.  
 
For context, after 2 days of back to back recruiting meetings and setting up our office. I didn’t want to be rude so rather than getting gas I went straight to the office, figuring I’d have enough gas just to make it to a gas station.  
 
Once finished and all pumped up with all of our amazing agents, I was finally ready to head to the airport. Only issue is, I was completely out of gas. This 6 minute long video is absolute chaos. I had to take a scooter to a gas station miles away, the gas attendant didn’t speak English or understand me so I had to steal the gas tank ( brought it back ), ride on a scooter for miles with gallons of gas and a container on my lap. Fill the car up and then try to make my flight for my club championship.  
 
If you watch this and don’t laugh please let me know. Otherwise enjoy 6 mins of “only me”.  
 
#funny #sarasota #florida #realestate

#SmashToberForSarasota 💗🎗️- we have come up with a goal to raise $25,000 to donate to the American Cancer Society and a challenge to encourage others to get involved, have a little fun, and help us raise vital funds and awareness surrounding breast cancer. 
 
To help us reach our goal, we created the #SmashtoberForSarasota challenge and hashtag. The idea is to smash a pumpkin while saying the name of someone you’d like to honor, a survivor or an angel. And it does not have to be breast cancer-specific. We also ask you to tag us and nominate three people in your post or story to help spread the word. For every post and story, we will donate $10 toward our goal of $25,000.  
 
At our grand opening on October 12th, we will have signature cocktails, a ribbon cutting, and much much more. If you cannot donate monetarily, helping us spread awareness by doing the challenge and nominating others would mean the world to us. Thank you for taking the time, and god bless. 💗🎗️ 
 
#breastcancerawareness #sarasota #Smashtoberforsarasota

3 years ago we were fortunate enough to join the signature family. A boutique brokerage on Long Island-.We joined because the same way they believed in us, we believed in them. They’re shared vision of giving back, white glove client service, and going the extra mile to ensure the happiness of their agents:  Instead of marketing money or an egregious split, I simply asked them to allow me to be myself, and to hear out some of our crazy ideas. ( sometimes I wonder if they would have preferred the first option ). 
 
But they did just that. And there is no surprise that there are now some of the biggest and best teams working there, it is no surprise they went from a small 10 person brokerage to number 1 in Suffolk county with over 2,000 agents and 20 + locations in such a short period of time. As corny as it had sounded, “ happy people sell more homes “ was always something they reiterated to me. And it remains to be true.  
 
They have kept their promise, and allowed me to be me. They have been there for us for better or for worse. They have taught me that when people go low, you go high. And they have welcomed us, truly not only into the signature family, but have made us feel as though we are their family. 
 
And Speaking of family and our crazy ideas. @joncariello_ and I have been through just about everything together. College, work after college, working back on the island together. ( Fun fact Jon and I actually wanted to be Dj’s when we were in college. We landed our first “ gig “ to open for a pretty big name at the House of blues in Myrtle beach. We skipped class for a week, closed the blinds at Jons house and tried to come up with what we thought was the best set ever! Not a single person showed up. Not one. There’s a picture lol ) from that to Then getting into real estate and forming the team With @justinsoriano.realestate ..

The formula for success is relatively simple: Surround yourself with the right people. Alone, no matter how good of a person you are, or how good at your job you are. Together, with others, you can achieve the unimaginable.

I am fortunate to have the opportunity to pursue my dreams, to learn, to grow, and to make a difference in this world not alone, but with people I consider family. It’s a privilege I do not take lightly, and I am reminded that gratitude is not just a fleeting emotion but a powerful perspective that can transform our lives and those of others around us. 

This announcement is a reminder to be present, to appreciate the people and experiences that enrich our journey, and to let life unfold as it should. The energy you put out you will receive 10 fold. People you never expected to meet will be brought into your life. 

When you put good into the world, good comes back. I am not sure how we got so lucky, but I am beyond fortunate to welcome these absolute rockstar, top agents with some of the most incredible stories and hearts to our @theoneilteam_ _ family. I cannot wait for you all to meet them, and see how special they are. To their clients, agents, and community. I truly do not know how I am so lucky, but today will be a day I will remember forever. Please welcome @smarkbreit @annglaves @semirmp @realchriswiseman to the family! Oh and their 4 new listings 😆. LFG!!!

Today a dream of mine has finally become a reality. Philanthropy and giving back was instilled in me even as a child. From soup kitchens on Sundays before I was even old enough to understand what I was doing.   
  
From High school, to college and first obtaining my real estate license. Philanthropy, giving back and community involvement has always been one of our core values. 
  
We have all lost too many friends and family members alike to mental illness, to cancer, drugs ETC. During good times and bad- I have always journaled: and what has always remained true is that what has always brought me the most joy, was not only giving back - but also simply making someone else smile.   
  
You never know what someone is going through. And sometimes we get caught up in our busy day to day that we forget to check in, make a call, return a call - or remind people how much we care and love them. Or even just a simple smile to a stranger.   
  
So while this has been a goal of mine for years - I have finally came up with the name and the mission.  
  
Make someone smile today, because it's contagious.  
  
The world is in a tough place right now, there are a lot of people struggling. Fiscally but also maybe mentally. It finally dawned on that me that although I am creating this go fund me and 501c non profit -  to be able to give back to those less fortunate, organizations, single mothers shopping for their children during the holidays, cancer awareness ETC - but also, that you don't need money or anything to make someone smile. In-fact, it is scientifically proven if you simply make yourself smile, it can trick your brain into a state of happiness and joy.  
  
My goal is not only to give back and raise awareness and help others - but to serve as a reminder. For you to smile, and in by doing so - you will make others smile too. Because You don't need money, or a social media following to make a difference.  
  
A simple smile or act of kindness, can go a long way.  
  
Make someone smile today, because it's contagious. God bless ❤️

Make someone smile today, it’s contagious. Part 1.

During the week of the grand opening in Florida, I was having an absolute panic attack. Having a very “”””bad day””””,  I was racing around I had gotten a haircut all week and honestly forgot. I get my haircut by the same person, every week for basically the last 10 years. I had reached out to the barbershop closest to me with them only being open for 5 more mins. I begged the person on the other line to stay open and I would be there in 10 mins. I raced there, expressed how anxious I was ETC. Jay and I started talking and hit it off, had a lot in common, he was new to the area and we talked while he gave me an incredible haircut for over an hour. We hit it off for sure. He made me smile, we were laughing, and completely changed my mood – I invited him to the grand opening next day and he had mentioned he had a baby on the way. 
 
I don’t have many friends down there yet, and not thinking he would ever come, when he walked into the party the next night it absolutely made my night. 
 
So, with that – My next time in town it was only fitting to return the favor. He doesn’t / didn’t need or want any of this – but I wanted to show him how much I appreciated his kind gesture, and return the favor. If you need a haircut hit up – thank you for your service, for the cut and for being someone I can now call a friend. 
 
Make someone smile today, its contagious

Make someone smile today, part 2. Today I showed a house for Amanda, and as I was locking up I noticed the neighbor was Vibing in her car for some time.  
 
I wanted to say something to her because I know all about staying in the car until the end of a song all too well but before I could she rolled her window down and complimented me on my car.  
 
We started talking and it turns out, she was in her car listening to gospel music because this week and season is extra tough for her and her family and She had just gotten back from church.  
 
I told her about the initiative and if could take her shopping, anywhere she wanted. 
 
She is such a sweetheart she actually took me to family dollar. She could have taken me to Kay jewelers lol! We went to stop and shop and the rest is history. She has 8 grandchildren, and this season is even more difficult because she lost a child to a car accident who was 17 years old.  
 
This is a tough time for a lot of people. I’m not posting this, or doing this for any other reason than because it makes me happy. I cried but it makes me happy to be able to help and be a friend to a stranger. Or to use my platform or my blessings to help someone in need. Or to motivate and inspire or remind others - you can make a difference and , the best part is, you don’t need money or social media to make to give back. Just make someone smile, because it’s contagious. I know she will pay it forward.  
 
God bless  ❤️
